WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-PT

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:01.334
In Return of the Ancients,

00:00:01.334 --> 00:00:05.672
we've added, for the first time, a
set of challenges to a Path of Exile 2 league.

00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.574
For every two challenges you complete,

00:00:07.574 --> 00:00:10.193
you'll receive a piece of the
Knight of Aldur armor set,

00:00:10.193 --> 00:00:11.795
so it's worth a try.

00:00:12.362 --> 00:00:15.148
To check your progress and
the requirements to complete a challenge,

00:00:15.148 --> 00:00:17.801
simply press "H" to open the challenges screen.

00:00:17.951 --> 00:00:19.319
There are eight challenges in total,

00:00:19.319 --> 00:00:22.222
and they progress from very easy
to very difficult.

00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.923
To complete the Rune Hunt,

00:00:23.923 --> 00:00:26.626
you'll need to find traces with
an increasingly large number of slots

00:00:26.626 --> 00:00:28.595
and use them to craft new items.

00:00:29.229 --> 00:00:32.999
Creating seven spaces can be
quite challenging, with six waves of enemies,

00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:36.002
so attempting one of these fights
may require skill.

00:00:38.638 --> 00:00:39.639
Throughout the campaign,

00:00:39.639 --> 00:00:41.408
there are many optional bosses.

00:00:41.408 --> 00:00:42.959
To complete "The Hunter,"

00:00:42.959 --> 00:00:45.361
you will need to hunt six of them.

00:00:45.361 --> 00:00:49.282
The last two, Akthi, the Final Sting,
and Anundr, the Sand Worm,

00:00:49.282 --> 00:00:51.551
can be quite difficult to find
on the Khari Crossing.

00:00:52.185 --> 00:00:55.271
To find them,
follow the dry riverbed.

00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:57.073
You'll find their arena at the end.

00:00:58.558 --> 00:01:00.877
"Ascendant" requires you to obtain
all eight points

00:01:00.877 --> 00:01:03.880
of your Ascendancy class by
completing the Ascendancy trials.

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:06.766
Obtaining the final set of points
can be quite challenging.

00:01:06.766 --> 00:01:10.220
You will need to defeat Zarokh on the 4th level of the Trial of the Sekhemas

00:01:10.653 --> 00:01:14.390
or defeat the Trial Master of the Trial of Chaos by finding the three keys.

00:01:15.141 --> 00:01:16.960
Of the two options, the Trial of Chaos

00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:20.029
will take much longer, as you will have to complete the trial multiple times,

00:01:20.029 --> 00:01:22.549
but the Trial of the Sekhemas
is more challenging,

00:01:22.549 --> 00:01:25.151
so you will have to decide which of the
two paths to follow.

00:01:26.719 --> 00:01:28.138
"The Reliquary" is simple.

00:01:28.138 --> 00:01:30.573
Identify 50 different unique items.

00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.910
Are you having trouble finding unique items?

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.647
Jado, the Master of Atlas, has many skills
that make you a specialist in finding them.

00:01:39.749 --> 00:01:41.151
To complete "The Artisan,"

00:01:41.151 --> 00:01:43.720
you will need to use several different crafting items.

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.839
They all stem from encounters with traces.

00:01:47.240 --> 00:01:48.441
For "The Cartographer,"

00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:50.894
you will need to assign your entire Atlas tree.

00:01:51.177 --> 00:01:52.712
All 300 of us.

00:01:53.163 --> 00:01:56.883
You can do this slowly, completing
all the maps within the fortress.

00:01:56.916 --> 00:01:58.918
But there is another way as well.

00:01:58.918 --> 00:02:01.054
Each time you defeat the Arbiter of Divinity,

00:02:01.054 --> 00:02:05.175
you will gain the ability to automatically complete a large section of the fortress.

00:02:06.676 --> 00:02:09.679
Find the keys to the fight
by searching for citadels in the Atlas.

00:02:09.829 --> 00:02:12.832
Each one has large, bright beams
so you can see them in the fog.

00:02:13.032 --> 00:02:16.719
After fighting him four times,
the entire fortress will be complete.

00:02:17.871 --> 00:02:21.040
And last,
but certainly not least, "The Winner".

00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:24.010
This challenge requires defeating
three supreme bosses,

00:02:24.010 --> 00:02:25.478
the most difficult fights in the game.

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:27.030
Tangmazu,

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:28.097
the Bodach

00:02:28.097 --> 00:02:29.682
and the Vessel of Kulemak.

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:34.070
These are the supreme champions of the Delirium,
Ritual, and Abyss leagues,

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.190
so you'll need to complete all three quest lines to fulfill this challenge.

00:02:37.674 --> 00:02:39.909
One important thing about the
Vessel of Kulemak

00:02:39.909 --> 00:02:42.162
is that you need to defeat it with all your might.

00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.113
This means risking
the item during the boss fight

00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:46.716
by returning the finger
and defeating him anyway.

00:02:49.352 --> 00:02:50.303
As mentioned,

00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:53.223
for every two challenges completed, you will receive pieces of the armor set.

00:02:53.223 --> 00:02:55.675
Therefore, you don't need to do
all of them to get some rewards.

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:58.628
But if you do, you can
show off your prowess.

00:02:58.778 --> 00:03:02.715
Because everyone in the global chat or forums will be able to see how many challenges you've completed.

00:03:03.149 --> 00:03:05.835
You will also receive this totem decoration
for your haven,

00:03:05.835 --> 00:03:07.837
meaning that more people
who trade with you at any given time

00:03:07.837 --> 00:03:10.840
will be able to see that you were there
and that you conquered the league.

00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:15.361
Experience these challenges and much more on May 29th
with Return of the Ancients.

00:03:15.562 --> 00:03:17.463
Thanks for watching, and see you later!

